the smell of the hot dogs and, of course, the sticky mess inside the stall! I regularly can smell my wife crying every time we have one.

The hot dog tasted like a bad hamburger. It's dry and tough.

Perhaps in Syria we don't know how to make hot dogs, but they taste terrible!

Your best days were in Iraq, but Turkey produces almost all your junk food, so we know an unreliable product when we see one. We can't tell you how sad we are when our children ask for hot dogs and my wife cries! Please apologize to the American food industry for producing this subpar food.

I really hope you feel ashamed for your national dish. A kid's life doesn't have to be this bad.

The candy and soda and frozen foods that I've tasted are worse!

You Americans make the best machines, transportation, and weapons (don't tell your kids that), but somehow you haven't managed to make usable food!

How can you reconcile with a country that produces this junk -- junk that makes your children cry when they ask for more?

advertisement

Speaking of junk food, American efficiency is wasted here too. An ordinary hot dog feeds only three kids, and getting even three children in here is a challenge.

Let's put it this way. Imagine you had a big dog in the backyard. He's your pet. In the other room your child is crying because he has lost his favorite toy!
